Given the right surroundings
and encouragement,

200
00:18:45,749 --> 00:18:48,584
I'll bet that that man could run
our company

201
00:18:48,669 --> 00:18:51,045
as well as youryoung Winthorpe.

202
00:18:51,421 --> 00:18:54,382
Are we talking
about a wager, Randolph?

203
00:18:56,135 --> 00:18:59,929
I suppose you think Winthorpe,
say if he were to lose hisjob,

204
00:18:59,972 --> 00:19:02,932
would resort to holding up people
on the streets?

205
00:19:03,016 --> 00:19:06,477
No, I don't thinkjust losing hisjob
would be enough forWinthorpe.

206
00:19:06,562 --> 00:19:12,483
I think we'd have to heap a little more
misfortune on those narrow shoulders.

207
00:19:13,110 --> 00:19:18,281
If he lost hisjob and his home
and his fiancée and his friends,

208
00:19:18,782 --> 00:19:22,451
if he were somehow disgraced
and arrested by the police

209
00:19:22,536 --> 00:19:24,537
and thrown in jail, even,

210
00:19:25,956 --> 00:19:29,792
yes, I'm sure he'd take to crime
like a fish to water.

211
00:19:30,377 --> 00:19:32,962
You'd have to put him
in the wrong surroundings, of course,

212
00:19:33,005 --> 00:19:35,298
with the worst sort of people.

213
00:19:35,340 --> 00:19:38,968
I mean real scum, Randolph.

214
00:19:39,011 --> 00:19:41,012
We've done it before.

215
00:19:41,471 --> 00:19:44,098
This time it's in a good cause.

216
00:19:44,433 --> 00:19:46,434
How much do you want to bet?

217
00:19:46,643 --> 00:19:49,020
-The usual amount.
-Why not?

218
00:19:54,818 --> 00:19:57,820
You're so brave, Louis.

219
00:19:57,905 --> 00:20:00,573
Someone has to take a stand
against criminals like that.

220
00:20:00,657 --> 00:20:02,575
But he could have killed you.

221
00:20:02,659 --> 00:20:05,703
In such a situation,
you have no time to think.

222
00:20:05,787 --> 00:20:10,333
Instinct takes over.
It's either kill or be killed.

223
00:20:14,630 --> 00:20:16,881
